{"metadata":{"name":"Sunan Abu Dawud","section":{"2":{"eng-name":"Prayer (Kitab Al-Salat)","ara-name":"كتاب الصلاة"}},"section_detail":{"2":{"hadithnumber_first":391,"hadithnumber_last":1160,"arabicnumber_first":391,"arabicnumber_last":1160}}},"hadiths":[{"hadithnumber":658,"arabicnumber":658,"text":"Anas b. Malik said; the prophet (ﷺ) used to visit Umm Sulaim. Sometimes the time for prayer would come and he would pray on out carpet that was really a mat. She (Umm Sulaim) used to wash it with water","grades":[{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Muhammad Muhyi Al-Din Abdul Hamid","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Zubair Ali Zai","grade":"Sahih"}],"reference":{"book":2,"hadith":268},"chapter":{"id":94,"ara-name":"باب الصَّلاَةِ عَلَى الْحَصِيرِ","eng-name":"Praying On A Hasir (Large Mat)","isFirstHadith":false}}]}